    h1 About this template and how to use it

    p This template <strong>Event block listing (local assets)</strong> is available if you wish to create local calendar events for your site.&nbsp;

    p If you wish to promote your event to a wider audience you should post on <a href="events.unimelb.edu.au">events.unimelb.edu.au</a> and use the feed as described on the events.unimelb examples.

    p This event listing is using an <a href="http://manuals.matrix.squizsuite.net/calendar/chapters/upcoming-events-list">upcoming events list </a>&nbsp;and is set to show:&nbsp;

    ul
      li 360 events in the future
      li Maximum of 20 events

    ol
      li Add a new standard page to your site
      li From the metadata screen select the page template: Event block listing (local assets).&nbsp;
      li
        ' Fields that can be used are:&nbsp;
        ul
          li Header text
          li Header subline
          li Banner image
          li Introductory text
      li Create single calendar events under this asset and they will automatically be listed on this page.

    h3 Adding calendar events

    p When adding local calendar events they should be:&nbsp;

    ul.ticked-list
      li Single Calendar Events (recurring calendar events needs some further work)
      li Type 2 (don't show in menu)
      li Asset status needs to be <strong>Live </strong>to be included on the event listing page
      li Only future upcoming events show

    p Optional settings:

    ul
      li Thumbnail image (set on details screen)
      li Contact details (set on metadata screen)
      li Location details &nbsp;(set on metadata screen)

